<H3> <TI>   USOR Members Disrupt Plenary Session </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    USOR Members Disrupt Plenary Session </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   AB2804220594 Kinshasa Tele-Zaire Television Network in 
French 1910 GMT 28 Apr 94 </F>

<F P=103> AB2804220594 </F>
<F P=104>  Kinshasa Tele-Zaire Television Network </F>
<F P=105>  French </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] We just received a report from one of our 
correspondents on the plenary session at the Palais du Peuple 
where the High Council of the Republic-Transitional Parliament 
[HCR-TP] was supposed to submit a report on its activities since 
the expiration of the 19 April deadline. The results were 
eagerly awaited by the Zairian people this afternoon. In 
accordance with Parliament regulations, the deliberations should 
have and could have immediately begun. However, when the 
members filled the conference room, and after the bureau was 
installed, about 20 members of the Sacred Union of the Radical 
Opposition [USOR] moved in to prevent the session from starting 
by whistling, booing, chanting and singing. 
  Up to 1830, the members of the HCR-PT bureau were unable to 
utter one word. They could not even announce the points on the 
agenda or begin the session. Some HCR-PT members left the room 
discouraged but some were there until 1930. The Tele-Zaire team 
was prevented from filming because their flashbulbs were broken. 
After the bulbs were replaced, the team was able to film some 
images which we will show you as soon as possible. 

</TEXT>

