<H3> <TI>   Armed Abductors Release Sudanese Ambassador </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Armed Abductors Release Sudanese Ambassador </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   EA2704172994 Omdurman Republic of Sudan Radio Network in 
Arabic 1300 GMT 27 Apr 94 </F>

<F P=103> EA2704172994 </F>
<F P=104>  Omdurman Republic of Sudan Radio Network </F>
<F P=105>  Arabic </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] The Sudanese ambassador to Somalia, 'Abd-al-Baqi 
Muhammad Hasan Ahmad, who was abducted on 19 April by an armed 
group belonging to the Hawadle clan, was released today in 
Mogadishu. Reports confirmed that the ambassador was in good 
health. 
  The ambassador, in a statement to a SUDAN NEWS AGENCY 
correspondent, expressed his thanks and appreciation to all 
those concerned with his case throughout his abduction. He 
stated that he would soon leave Mogadishu for Khartoum. Sudan's 
ambassador to Somalia is the only Arab ambassador who has been 
present in Mogadishu throughout the developments in Somalia. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

