<F P=100> EAST AFRICA </F>
<F P=101> Tanzania </F>
<H3> <TI>   Foreign Ministry Denies Rwandan Border Closure </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Foreign Ministry Denies Rwandan Border Closure </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   EA2904111094 Dar es Salaam Radio Tanzania Network in Swahili 
0700 GMT 29 Apr 94 </F>

<F P=103> EA2904111094 </F>
<F P=104>  Dar es Salaam Radio Tanzania Network </F>
<F P=105>  Swahili </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Tanzania has denied a media report that it is paying 
little attention to Rwandan citizens being killed by government 
soldiers. An officer of the Rwandan Patriotic Front reportedly 
said that Tanzania has closed its borders with Rwanda, an act 
which he said is unlawful against innocent Rwandan civilians who 
are being killed. The story was carried by the Uganda DAILY 
ROCKET on 25 April. 
  A statement by the Ministry of Foreign Affairs and 
International Cooperation said the story on Tanzania closing its 
border with Rwanda is baseless because large numbers Rwandan 
citizens cross into Tanzania's Kagera Region almost daily. On 
Tanzania's move to station troops alongside its border with 
Rwanda, the statement said the action was taken to safeguard 
Tanzanian citizens and their properties along the border. It is 
not for any other purpose, the statement added. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

