<F P=100> REPUBLIC OF SOUTH AFRICA </F>
<H3> <TI>   Western Transvaal Districts Declared `Unrest Areas' </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Western Transvaal Districts Declared `Unrest Areas' </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   MB2804194694 Johannesburg SAPA in English 1930 GMT 28 Apr 94 </F>
<F P=103> MB2804194694 </F>
<F P=104>  Johannesburg SAPA </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [Report by A. Thomson] </F>
  [Text] Pretoria April 28 SAPA -- Fifteen magisterial 
districts in the Western Transvaal were on Thursday [28 April] 
declared unrest areas, SABC [South African Broadcasting 
Corporation] radio news reported. The areas, listed in a special 
Government Gazette, include Ventersdorp, Potchefstroom, 
Lichtenburg, Schweizer-Reneke, Klerksdorp, Rustenburg, Koster 
and Christiana. 
  The Gazette gave no reasons for the declaration. 
  Earlier on Thursday Afrikaner Weerstandsbeweging [AWB, 
Afrikaner Resistance Movement] supporters gathered near 
Rustenburg to pledge support for Afrikaner freedom. 
  Police later confirmed right-wingers were also gathering 
near 
Koster. They said they were monitoring the movements of AWB 
supporters. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

