<H3> <TI>   Diplomatic Relations Established With Zimbabwe </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Diplomatic Relations Established With Zimbabwe </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   MB2904065694 Johannesburg Radio South Africa Network in 
English 0500 GMT 29 Apr 94 </F>

<F P=103> MB2904065694 </F>
<F P=104>  Johannesburg Radio South Africa Network </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Zimbabwe and South Africa have established 
diplomatic relations at ambassadorial level. The two countries 
have for many years been represented at trade mission level. 
Zimbabwean Foreign AFfairs Minister Nathan Shamuyarira said the 
basis of the new diplomacy was South Africa's interim 
constitution which came into effect earlier this week. The new 
relations come into affect today. 

</TEXT>

