<H3> <TI>   Violent Incidents Reported at Polling Stations </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Violent Incidents Reported at Polling Stations </PHRASE></F></HT>
<H4>    Grenade Found on Suspected MK Member </H4>

<F P=102> MB2904100694 Johannesburg SAPA in English 0927 GMT 29 Apr 94 </F>
<F P=103> MB2904100694 </F>
<F P=104>  Johannesburg SAPA </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] East London April 29 SAPA -- A suspected member of 
African National Congress military wing, Umkhonto we Sizwe 
[Spear of the Nation], has been arrested after being found 
carrying a hand grenade at a polling station in Duncan Village, 
reports SABC [South African Broadcasting Corporation] radio 
news. East London police confirmed that six men claiming to be 
ANC election monitors had tried to gain access to a guarded 
building housing sealed ballot boxes. When they were confronted 
by the security forces, one of the men fled, dropping a machine 
pistol. The grenade was found on another man. 

</TEXT>

