<H4>    Suspected Right-Wingers Arrested </H4>

<F P=102> MB2904123094 Johannesburg SAPA in English 1202 GMT 29 Apr 94 </F>
<F P=103> MB2904123094 </F>
<F P=104>  Johannesburg SAPA </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [Report by K. Swart] </F>
  [Text] Pretoria April 29 SAPA -- Seven men with possible 
rightwing links have been arrested at Betanie in the Odi Region, 
police in Bophuthatswana said on Friday [29 April]. A police 
spokesman said the men had allegedly attempted to intimidate 
Betanie residents into not voting, SABC [South African 
Broadcasting Corporation] radio news reported. 

</TEXT>

