<F P=100> CENTRAL AFRICA </F>
<F P=101> Burundi </F>
<H3> <TI>   Disarmament Begins in Bujumbura; Gunfire Still Heard </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Disarmament Begins in Bujumbura; Gunfire Still Heard </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   EA2804212094 Bujumbura Radio-Television Nationale du Burundi 
Radio in Kirundi 1700 GMT 28 Apr 94 </F>

<F P=103> EA2804212094 </F>
<F P=104>  Bujumbura Radio-Television Nationale du Burundi 
Radio </F>

<F P=105>  Kirundi </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] The work of disarming citizens who are in possession 
of illegal arms officially began today. It began in the 
Bujumbura suburbs of Kinama, Cibitoke, and Mutakura. 
  We can still hear gunshots in the northern suburbs of 
Bujumbura town. 

</TEXT>

