<F P=101> East Region </F>
<H3> <TI>   Shandong Secretary Praises First Non-Imported Cement Plant </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Shandong Secretary Praises First Non-Imported Cement Plant </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   SK3103071394 Jinan Shandong People's Radio Network in 
Mandarin 2300 GMT 30 Mar 94 </F>

<F P=103> SK3103071394 </F>
<F P=104>  Jinan Shandong People's Radio Network </F>
<F P=105>  Mandarin </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Lunan Cement Plant, China's first modernized large 
cement enterprise to use domestically produced equipment 
designed in China, and to be furnished with two new production 
lines, formally passed the state acceptance test on 30 March. 
This is a breakthrough in China's large cement industry as well 
as a milestone in the history of developments in the building 
materials industry. This has also put an end to China's long 
history of importing modernized cement production lines from 
abroad. The construction of the Lunan Cement Plant is a key 
project of the state during the Seventh Five-Year Plan period. 
All the major equipment of this plant was produced by China 
itself. The two new production lines with a daily production 
capacity of 2,000 tonnes of clinker [words indistinct] are 
designed to produce 1.3 million tonnes of cement annually. 
  Zou Jiahua, vice premier of the State Council; and Wang 
Guangying, Lei Jieqiong, and Lu Jiaxi, vice chairmen of the 
National People's Congress Standing Committee, wrote 
inscriptions for and congratulated Lunan Cement Plant on its 
receipt of state approval. Jiang Chunyun, secretary of the 
provincial party committee, sent a congratulatory message to the 
plant. (Zhang Renwei), director of the State Building Materials 
Bureau, and Li Wenquan, deputy secretary of the provincial party 
committee, attended the completion ceremony. 

</TEXT>

