<F P=100> NATIONAL AFFAIRS </F>
<F P=101> Political &amp; Social </F>
<H3> <TI>   Beijing Government Officials Promote `Hope Project' </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Beijing Government Officials Promote `Hope Project' </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   OW3003120794 Beijing XINHUA in English 1133 GMT 30 Mar 94 </F>
<F P=103> OW3003120794 </F>
<F P=104>  Beijing XINHUA </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Beijing, March 30 (XINHUA) -- Government 
departments in the capital launched a campaign titled "every 
citizen is a cornerstone of the Hope Project" here today. 
  Chen Xitong, secretary of the Beijing municipal committee of 
the Communist Party of China, Beijing Mayor Li Qiyan and other 
government officials made donations at the newly-established 
Beijing Donation Center for the Hope Project. 
  "The Hope Project will be full of hope when all the people 
are mobilized," Zhang Jianmin, director of the municipal 
people's congress said. 
  When a center worker asked Mayor Li Qiyan whether he would 
like to aid a boy or girl, he answered: "It makes no difference 
as long as it can help an out-of-school child." 
  In poverty-stricken areas of China, only 300 yuan are needed 
to help a child through a year of schooling. 
  Since the Hope Project, a national effort to help send 
children back to school in poor areas, was launched about a 
decade ago, governments at various levels, social bodies and 
common people have donated to it. 
  More than 2,000 people took part in the campaign today and 
donated more than 100,000 yuan. 

</TEXT>

