<H3> <TI>   Handbook on Anticorruption Policy Published </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Handbook on Anticorruption Policy Published </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   OW3103051094 Beijing Central Television Program One Network 
in Mandarin 1400 GMT 3 Mar 94 </F>

<F P=103> OW3103051094 </F>
<F P=104>  Beijing Central Television Program One Network 
in Mandarin 1400 GMT 3 Mar 94 </F>

<F P=105> Mandarin </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [From the "News" program] </F>
  [Text] To support efforts to carry out the anticorruption 
struggle in depth, the China (Fang Zheng) Publishing House has 
published the Handbook on Anticorruption Policy, Laws, and 
Regulations. The book was compiled by the Office of Law 
and Regulations of the Central Discipline Inspection Commission; 
relevant anticorruption policies, laws, and regulations in six 
categories are included in the book. 
  Cao Qingze, deputy secretary of the Central Discipline 
Inspection Commission and minister of supervision, wrote the 
book's foreword. 

