<F P=100> NATIONAL AFFAIRS </F>
<F P=101> Political &amp; Social </F>
<H3> <TI>   Guiyang Prisoners Escape, Kill 12 Policemen </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Guiyang Prisoners Escape, Kill 12 Policemen </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   HK3103103994 Hong Kong CHENG MING in Chinese No 198, 1 Apr 94 </F>
<F P=103> HK3103103994 </F>
<F P=104>  Hong Kong CHENG MING </F>
<F P=105>  Chinese </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> ["Reference news" by Lei Hsi (7191 2497): "Prisoners in </F>
Guiyang Stage a Rebellion] 
  [Text] On the morning of 2 March, prisoners working on a 
construction site on a highway near Huaxi Reservoir, Guiyang, 
staged a rebellion. They disarmed armed policemen with their 
tools and shouted: "Run for your lives!" Over 300 of the 500 
prisoners ran into the hills. 
  Sources said that 12 armed policemen were beaten to death 
and 
over 100 prisoners were placed on the wanted list. Latest 
sources have disclosed that 30 or so prisoners are still at 
large. The cause of the rebellion was that the prisoners could 
not tolerate the heavy workload. Prior to this, they had always 
been slack in work. These prisoners were criminal prisoners for 
terms of 15 years or more, and their age range is between 20 to 
30. 

</TEXT>

