<F P=100> HONG KONG &amp; MACAO </F>
<F P=101> Hong Kong </F>
<H3> <TI>   Jiang Zemin Meets Hong Kong Press Chiefs </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Jiang Zemin Meets Hong Kong Press Chiefs </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   OW3003134194 Beijing XINHUA in English 1310 GMT 30 Mar 94 </F>
<F P=103> OW3003134194 </F>
<F P=104>  Beijing XINHUA </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Beijing, March 30 (XINHUA) -- Chinese President 
Jiang Zemin encouraged major Hong Kong-based newspapers and 
magazines to contribute even more to the prosperity and peaceful 
transition of the territory. 
  The president made the remark here today during a meeting 
with the visiting chief executives of the Hong Kong "WEN WEI 
PO," "TA KUNG PAO," "HONG KONG COMMERCIAL DAILY," "NEW EVENING 
POST," "ZIJIN MAGAZINE" and "ECONOMIC INFORMATION AND AGENCY." 
  Jiang hoped that the newspapers and magazines would further 
improve, love the motherland including Hong Kong, protect the 
interests of Hong Kong residents and promote the peaceful 
transition of the territory in line with the basic principle of 
"one country and two systems." 
  The chief executives arrived here yesterday at the 
invitation 
of the Information Office of the State Council, the Hong Kong 
and Macao Affairs Office of the State Council and the Hong Kong 
branch of the XINHUA NEWS AGENCY. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

