BFN 

  [Text] Within the framework of his visit to the PRC, Dr. 
Ivo Sanader, deputy minister of foreign affairs of the Republic 
of Croatia, has visited the city of Shenzhen in southern China, 
the Croatian Embasssy in Beijing announced. 
  Officials from the Chinese Ministry of Foreign Affairs and 
Shenzhen's deputy mayor acquainted Dr. Sanader and Croatian 
Ambassador Andrija Kojakovic with the economic situation in the 
city. The talks focused on ways to develop economic cooperation 
between Croatia and China. Views were exchanged about common 
experienece in joint foreign capital investments. The Chinese 
hosts were particularly keen to learn about the privatization 
process in Croatia. 

