BFN 

  [Text] Guangzhou, March 14 (CNS) -- Romanian President Mr. 
Ion Iliescu said today during his visit to Guangdong that 
Romania would establish a permanent presence in the province to 
strengthen cooperation between China and Romania. 
  The president and his party left for Romania this afternoon 
after a four-day visit to Shenzhen, Zhuhai and Guangzhou. 
  Vice Governor of Guangdong Mr. Lu Ruihua met the Romanian 
party last night. He gave an account of the province's recent 
economic development and said he welcomed Romanian investment 
and cooperation in the province. 
  Mr. Iliescu said he was very glad to see Guangdong's 
economic 
achievements and that Romania planned to set up a permanent 
presence there to strengthen exchange and cooperation with China. 

